cofigmaps can be created in 4 ways
1) literal
2) file
3) env file 
4) manifes

1) literal 
    kubectl create cm cm1 --literal-from=name=vijay --literal-from=passwd=vijay
2) file
   eg: file
          hi this is vijay having contecta
   kubectl create cm cm1 --literal-file=file

3) file
   eg: file
          hi this is vijay having contecta
   kubectl create cm cm1 --literal-env-file=file


4) file
   eg: manifest.yaml

        
         
   kubectl create cm1 -f manifest.yaml







1️⃣ Literal
kubectl create configmap cm1 --from-literal=name=vijay --from-literal=passwd=vijay

2️⃣ From file
kubectl create configmap cm1 --from-file=data.txt

3️⃣ From env file
kubectl create configmap cm1 --from-env-file=app.env

4️⃣ From manifest YAML
kubectl apply -f manifest.yaml